President Obama has nominated Judge Adalberto José Jordán to the United States Court of Appeals for the Eleventh Circuit. The President praised Judge Jordán's commitment to fairness and judicial integrity. Judge Jordán currently serves as a District Judge in the Southern District of Florida and has been teaching law at the University of Miami School of Law since 1990. He was born in Havana, Cuba, and immigrated to the United States at the age of six. Judge Jordán has an impressive legal career and has presided over nearly 200 trials on a variety of civil and criminal matters.